headline: Super Micro Computer, T-Mobile, Samsung: 3 Stocks in Focus
summary: Super Micro Computer (SMCI) must submit its delayed 10-K filing to the Securities and Exchange Commission to avoid being delisted. T-Mobile (TMUS) was reported among several telecommunications companies to be hacked by Chinese intelligence agencies, according to The Wall Street Journal. Samsung (005930.KS) shares gain after the company announced a $7 billion buyback over the course of the next year. To watch more expert insights and analysis on the latest market action, check out more Morning Brief here. This post was written by Naomi Buchanan.

headline: Apple ups satellite investment stakes with latest Globalstar deal
summary: Apple’s move to raise its ante on extended D2D satellite connectivity services by another $1.5bn will up the stakes for both its OEM competitors and the MNO partner channel, which is searching for its own D2D differentiation.
